title: Phtheochroa fulviplicana
text:
Phtheochroa fulviplicana is a species of <a href="moth">moth</a> of the family <a href="Tortricidae">Tortricidae</a>. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from <a href="Maine">Maine</a>, <a href="Alberta">Alberta</a>, <a href="Nevada">Nevada</a> and <a href="California">California</a>.
The <a href="wingspan">wingspan</a> is 14–23 mm. Adults have been recorded on wing from May to July and in December.
